  "prompt": "What is the best way to teach your baby to read?",
  "response": "Teaching a baby to read requires a gentle, age-appropriate approach. Here are some effective strategies:\n\n1. Read to your baby regularly\n- Start reading aloud from infancy\n- Use picture books with simple, colorful images\n- Point to words and pictures as you read\n\n2. Make reading interactive\n- Use animated voices\n- Ask questions about the pictures\n- Encourage interaction and engagement\n\n3. Use phonics and letter recognition\n- Teach letter sounds\n- Use alphabet books\n- Play letter recognition games\n\n4. Use age-appropriate methods\n- For babies: Focus on exposure and enjoyment\n- For toddlers: Introduce basic letter recognition\n- For preschoolers: Start simple word recognition\n\n5. Use helpful tools\n- Alphabet blocks\n- Flashcards\n- Educational videos\n- Reading apps designed for young children\n\n6. Create a positive environment\n- Make reading fun\n- Be patient\n- Praise and encourage efforts\n\n7. Recommended techniques\n- Sight word recognition\n- Phonemic awareness\n- Repeated exposure to words and letters\n\nImportant notes:\n- Every child learns differently\n- Don't rush the process\n- Keep activities enjoyable\n- Consult pediatric experts for personalized advice\n\nRemember, the goal is to foster a love of reading, not to pressure your child.",
